    ],
    "http://schema.org/url": [
      {
        "@id": "https://ww1.ticketpro.ca/event.php?event_id=7394"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "Diffusion gratuite du match 5 des Canadiens contre le Lightning"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": " <p><strong>Free live broadcast of Game 5 on the big screen</strong></p>\n\n<p>As the city pulses with hockey fever following the massive success of our last screening, Espace St-Denis is thrilled to announce that it will once again open the doors of Studio St-Denis to the public for a free broadcast of the game this Wednesday, April 29.</p>\n\n<p>Espace St-Denis invites Montrealers to trade their living room couches for the roar of the crowd in a high-energy collective experience. The game will be projected on a high-definition screen, offering an immersive experience that puts you right in the heart of the action. All you need to do is reserve your spot!</p>\n\n<p><strong>Event details:</strong></p>\n\n<p>• <strong>What:</strong> Free broadcast of Game 5: Montreal vs. Tampa Bay</p>\n\n<p>• <strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, April 29, 2026. Doors: 5:30 p.m. | Pre-game: 6:00 p.m. | Game: 7 p.m.</p>\n\n<p>• <strong>Where:</strong> Studio St-Denis (1594 Saint-Denis Street, Montreal)</p>\n\n<p>• <strong>Admission:</strong> Free entry, but online reservation is mandatory (maximum of 4 tickets per person).</p>\n\n<p>• <strong>On-site:</strong> Bar service and game-day snacks will be available.</p>\n\n<p>Admission is on a first-come, first-served basis; guests are encouraged to arrive early to secure the best seats.</p>\n<style>\n@media screen and (max-width: 600px){iframe{width:100%;}}\n.location-page-temp {display: block!important;}\n</style>"
      }
    ],
