    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>A new era in live entertainment has arrived. K-POP ♾ INFINITY is a bold, high-energy live concert experience inspired by the global K-Pop phenomenon and the cinematic world of K-Pop Demon Hunters. </p>\n\n<p>Audiences can expect spectacular performances featuring music inspired by the worlds of Huntr/x and the Saja Boys, alongside iconic hits from BTS, BLACKPINK, TWICE, KATSEYE, Stray Kids, and many more of K-Pop's biggest global stars. </p>\n\n<p>Blending the electrifying energy of contemporary K-Pop with the scale and polish of West End stagecraft, K-POP ♾ INFINITY features eight elite singer-dancers, cutting-edge visual design, and a powerful live sound experience. The result is a fully immersive 75-minute production that delivers precision, passion, and spectacle in equal measure. </p>\n\n<p>Set within the world of the futuristic Infinity Academy, the production uses theatrical staging, visual storytelling, and thematic elements to frame the concert experience. Throughout the show, themes of friendship, identity, unity, and self-expression are explored through music, choreography, and atmosphere — creating an emotional and visually striking journey without interrupting the momentum of a live pop concert. </p>\n\n<p>Created and written by award-winning West End star Elesha Paul Moses (TINA - The Tina Turner Musical) alongside long-time collaborator Steven Fulcher, K-POP ♾ INFINITY merges East Asian performance precision with Western stagecraft, redefining what a modern pop concert can be. </p>\n\n<style>\n.location-page-temp {\n    display: block!important;\n}\n</style>"
      }
    ],
